sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_R0184
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A mutant version of the T7lac promoter designed by Dubendorff and Studier. The promoter is based on the strong ??10 T7 promoter but incorporates an A->C mutation at -16. The LacI operator site is a partially symmetric 25bp sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The -16 mutation was included to weaken the consensus promoter as described by Imburgio and co-workers (see BBa_R0183 for more information)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is based on the T7lac promoter described by Dubendorff and Studier (JMB 1991, 219, 45-59). The only modification is the mutation at -16.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_R0185
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A lac repressible T7 promoter. This promoter is similar to those found in the pET vectors with T7lac promoters. I mutated the -10 base to a G, which should make it about 4% of the strength of consensus. The base numbering is as used by Studier and coworkers (JMB 1991, 219, 45-59). See BBa_R0183 for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The -10 mutation from consensus was included to weaken the consensus promoter as described by Imburgio and co-workers (see BBa_R0183 for more information)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is based on the T7lac promoter described by Dubendorff and Studier (JMB 1991, 219, 45-59). The only modification is the mutation at -10.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K113010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Wu Jingjing, Wang Jinyu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Two T7 promoters are reversely overlapping.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is difficult to make this short DNA by PCR as both sides are T7 promoters, which are very similar. It is highly possible that they form loops before they can be synthesized by PCR. Thus we order two single stranded DNA and then anneal them together by touchdown PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of T7 promoter is TAATACGACTCACTATA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K113011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Wu Jingjing, Wang Jinyu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Two T7 promoters are reversely overlapping in five base pairs, with the third one mutated from A to G.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is difficult to make this short DNA by PCR as both sides are T7 promoters, which are very similar. It is highly possible that they form loops before they can be synthesized by PCR. Thus we order two single stranded DNA and then anneal them together by touchdown PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of T7 promoter is TAATACGACTCACTATA (from 5' to 3').

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K731722

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Depetris, Giacomo Giacomelli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the B0010 part extracted by PCR from the doulbe terminator B0012. We didn't manage to extract it directly from the registry and we discovered that others had the same problem; for this reason we are submitting it once again, confirmed by sequencing and by experience...ready to use! The characterization has been done both with T7 and Coli RNApolymerases.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: I don't have any design considerations, anyway it is useful to use TBE1X instead of TAE1X to make screening gels of such small fragments.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part comes from B0012 contained in E0840, a double terminator in which B0010 is the second one. We used an extraction PCR.
